#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2488
msgid ""
"By default, Ren'Py will now use the arguments supplied to a screen in the "
"``show screen`` and ``call screen`` statements to predict the screen. This "
"is potentially dangers, as it means that if either statement has side "
"effects, those side effects will occur as part of screen prediction. To "
"mitigate this problem, both statements now take a ``nopredict`` clause that "
"prevents screen prediction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2495
msgid ""
"Ren'Py will now attempt to predict images inside if clauses that would not "
"be taken, and will ignore errors that occur during statement prediction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2498
msgid ""
"A pair of functions, :func:`renpy.start_predict_screen` and :func:`renpy."
"stop_predict_screen` allows for manual prediction of time images that will "
"be used by screens, including parameterized screens."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2502
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now supports profiling of screens, via the :func:`renpy."
"profile_screen` function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2505
msgid ""
"Ren'Py has been changed to make a copy of the screens being displayed before "
"a transition occurs. This makes it possible to use a transition to show "
"screen updates. For example, one could increase the value displayed by a "
"bar, and then use the dissolve transition to dissolve in the new segment of "
"bar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2512 ../../source/changelog.rst:4119
msgid "Image Prediction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2514
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now has a supported mechanism for manually predicting images in cases "
"where automatic image prediction fails. This mechanism consists of two "
"functions: :func:`renpy.start_predict` starts prediction of images, while :"
"func:`renpy.stop_predict` stops prediction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2520
msgid "Accessibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2522
msgid ""
"Ren'Py now includes support for self-voicing, a mode in which Ren'Py will "
"read on-screen text to vision impaired players. To activate self-voicing, "
"press the ``v`` key.  For more information, please read the :ref:`self-"
"voicing <self-voicing>` documentation."
msgstr ""
"Ren'Py が自己発話に対応しました。このモードでは Ren'Py は視覚障害者に画面上の"
"テキストを読み上げるようになります。自己発話機能を有効にするには、``v`` キー"
"を押します。詳細は :ref:`self-voicing <self-voicing>` を参照してください。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2527
msgid ""
"The new :propref:`alt` style property allows one to supply alternative text "
"that allows Ren'Py to voice imagemap components and buttons with incomplete "
"names."
msgstr ""
"新しい :propref:`alt` スタイルプロパティーにより、イメージマップや名前が不完"
"全なボタンを Ren'Py が発話できるようする代替テキストが与えられるようになりま"
"す。"

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2531
msgid ""
"The Ren'Py launcher now includes a large-text mode that can be accessed from "
"the preferences page. This mode increases text size and contrast."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2535
msgid "Android In-App Purchasing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2537
msgid ""
"This version of Ren'Py includes a high-level interface that supports in-app "
"purchasing on the Android platform. This interface currently support Google "
"Play and the Amazon App Store."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2542
msgid "Pixel Art"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2544
msgid ""
"Ren'Py supports nearest-neighbor filtering of images. This ensures that "
"screen pixels correspond to a single texture pixel, which is the scaling "
"mode preferred for use with pixel art. Nearest-neighbor mode is enabled with "
"the new :tpref:`nearest` transform property."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/changelog.rst:2549
msgid ""
"The new :func:`config.adjust_view_size` callback makes it possible to set "
"the size of the Ren'Py viewport to something other than the size of the "
"window (or screen, in fullscreen mode). For example, a game can use this "
"callback to limit its viewport size to integer multiples of its native size."
msgstr ""

